<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<task id="067" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3">
  <metadata>
    <title>Hoist workspace section registry + builder to @spaarke/ui-components (ADR-012 compliance; Bug 2 fix)</title>
    <phase>F (Verification — remediation)</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>12</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>030, 034, 070</dependencies>
    <blocks>072</blocks>
    <tags>refactoring, shared-components, react, frontend, architecture</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Cross-solution refactor: moves code from LegalWorkspace solution into @spaarke/ui-components shared lib. Touches THREE solutions (LegalWorkspace, SpaarkeAi, the shared lib). FR-25/NFR-10 risk — standalone LegalWorkspace MUST continue to function identically. Multi-file dependency graph. Code-review + adr-check + dark-mode-audit required.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>none</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Cross-solution refactor — single agent or careful sequence required to preserve FR-25 (standalone LegalWorkspace untouched in behavior).</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Fix Bug 2 from operator smoke feedback AND address the ADR-012 cross-cutting-components
    limitation flagged by the project owner. Currently SpaarkeAi's WorkspaceHomeTab renders
    only structural placeholders (no section content) because the section registry and
    workspace-config builder live solution-local in LegalWorkspace. Hoist the portable parts
    of LegalWorkspace's workspace section infrastructure to @spaarke/ui-components so both
    LegalWorkspace (standalone) AND SpaarkeAi (embedded) render section content from a single
    source of truth.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React + TypeScript engineer comfortable with monorepo refactors, shared-library
    design, and Vite tsconfig path aliases. Familiar with React 19 hooks, Fluent v9, and
    the ADR-012 shared-component contract.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `@spaarke/ui-components` exports a workspace section infrastructure (buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig,
    SECTION_REGISTRY for portable factories, types). LegalWorkspace's sectionRegistry.ts is
    refactored to compose shared + local registrations. SpaarkeAi's WorkspaceHomeTab.tsx
    renders ACTUAL section content (not placeholders) by consuming the shared infrastructure.
    Standalone LegalWorkspace continues to render identically (FR-25 / NFR-10 preserved).
    The ADR-012 cross-cutting limitation flagged by the project owner is resolved for
    workspace section composition.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 030 (WorkspacePane LegalWorkspace embed) shipped structure-only Home tab content
      with a documented rationale: "Strict reuse of LegalWorkspace's SECTION_REGISTRY +
      buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig would require cross-solution coupling that SpaarkeAi does
      not currently have (package.json has no LegalWorkspace dependency). Per the parent
      agent message ('Your job is to land the foundational structure cleanly'), the Home
      tab renders a faithful structural representation of the user's layout — correct rows,
      correct column widths, correct section identities — with each section rendering a
      placeholder content body."

      Operator smoke at 2026-05-20 confirmed: "no data showing for the workspace widgets."
      Plus: "there was mention in earlier question about ADR limitation of cross cutting
      components — that needs to be addressed."

      Diagnostic agent analysis (read-only):
      - `WorkspaceHomeTab.tsx:184-222` (`buildFoundationalConfig`): each section is hardcoded
        type:"content" with a placeholder `renderContent`. This is the deliberate placeholder
        from task 030.
      - LegalWorkspace owns: `sectionRegistry.ts` (the registry array), 6 per-section
        `*.registration.ts` files in `sections/`, and `workspace/buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig.ts`
        (the pure builder, no LegalWorkspace-specific imports).
      - @spaarke/ui-components ALREADY owns: `WorkspaceShell`, `SectionPanel`, `ActionCard{Row}`,
        `MetricCard{Row}`, and ALL types (`SectionRegistration`, `SectionFactoryContext`,
        `SectionConfig`) per ADR-012.
      - `buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig` is PURE and TYPE-ONLY against the shared lib — hoisting
        is a pure relocation.
      - 4-5 section factories are PORTABLE (no LegalWorkspace-only imports). The `dailyBriefing`
        factory (task 034) uses local `useDailyBriefing` + `DailyBriefingSection` — stays in
        LegalWorkspace OR is also hoisted as part of this task (decision required during work).

      Effort estimate from diagnostic: medium (1-2 days). The risk is cross-solution build
      verification (LegalWorkspace MUST continue to build + render identically).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sectionRegistry.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/workspace/buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/getStarted.registration.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/quickSummary.registration.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/latestUpdates.registration.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/todo.registration.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/documents.registration.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sections/dailyBriefing/dailyBriefing.registration.ts</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceHomeTab.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/types.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">Shared components and shared logic live in @spaarke/ui-components. The workspace section registry + builder are cross-cutting infrastructure consumed by 2+ solutions — they BELONG in the shared lib. This task closes the gap.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 tokens only. No hex / rgba literals introduced.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 19 patterns. No legacy React 16 fallbacks.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No `accessToken` props in any new shared-lib code. All BFF calls (if any factories call BFF) use `authenticatedFetch` via passed-in `SectionFactoryContext` callbacks — NOT by importing `@spaarke/auth` into the shared lib (preserves ADR-012 boundary).</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-25 / NFR-10: Standalone LegalWorkspace MUST continue to function identically. After this task, opening standalone LegalWorkspace in a separate browser tab MUST show all 9 templates in its wizard AND render existing user layouts with the same section content as before.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">If a section factory has LegalWorkspace-specific dependencies (e.g., `dailyBriefing` uses local `useDailyBriefing` hook), EITHER (a) hoist the dependency too if it makes sense for shared-lib use, OR (b) keep that factory LegalWorkspace-local and compose into the LegalWorkspace registry alongside shared factories. Document the decision per-factory.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do NOT modify the `WorkspaceShell` component itself — it's already in the shared lib and consumed by both solutions.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">SpaarkeAi MUST consume the hoisted infrastructure via the shared-lib public barrel (`@spaarke/ui-components`), not via deep imports.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-pcf-platform-libraries.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/webresource/full-page-custom-page.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/spec.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/plan.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/drafts/012-actioncard-decision.md</file>
      <file>docs/guides/SHARED-UI-COMPONENTS-GUIDE.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="1" name="Inventory portable vs solution-local factories">
      For each of the 6 LegalWorkspace section factories, classify:
      - **Portable**: only imports from @spaarke/ui-components types + general utilities. Examples likely: getStarted (uses ActionCard which is already shared), quickSummary, latestUpdates, todo, documents.
      - **Solution-local**: imports from LegalWorkspace-specific components or hooks. Example: dailyBriefing (uses local DailyBriefingSection + useDailyBriefing).
      Document in `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/drafts/067-factory-inventory.md`.
    </step>
    <step order="2" name="Hoist buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig to shared lib">
      Move `src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/workspace/buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig.ts` to
      `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig.ts`.
      Update internal imports if needed (likely zero changes — diagnostic confirmed it's already type-only against shared lib).
      Export from `WorkspaceShell/index.ts` barrel AND root `index.ts`. Replace LegalWorkspace's local copy with a re-export from `@spaarke/ui-components` so existing imports don't break.
    </step>
    <step order="3" name="Hoist SYSTEM_DEFAULT_LAYOUT_JSON if applicable">
      Diagnostic mentioned `SYSTEM_DEFAULT_LAYOUT_JSON`. If it lives in LegalWorkspace and is referenced by buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig, hoist it too. Otherwise skip.
    </step>
    <step order="4" name="Hoist portable section factories">
      For each portable factory (inventory step 1):
      - Create `src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/sections/{name}.registration.ts`
      - Move the factory file contents (or carefully copy + delete the original)
      - Verify any component/utility imports resolve from `@spaarke/ui-components` (no LegalWorkspace paths)
      - Update LegalWorkspace's `sectionRegistry.ts` to import the hoisted registrations from `@spaarke/ui-components` (instead of local paths)
      - Verify LegalWorkspace builds clean after the move.
    </step>
    <step order="5" name="Decide on dailyBriefing factory placement">
      Two options for `dailyBriefing.registration.ts`:
      - **Option H (hoist)**: also hoist `useDailyBriefing.ts` + `DailyBriefingSection.tsx` to shared lib. SpaarkeAi gets Daily Briefing automatically. Trade-off: shared lib gains AI-feature dependency on `@spaarke/auth` (already there) + telemetry callback pattern.
      - **Option L (stay)**: factory stays in LegalWorkspace. SpaarkeAi's registry composition omits it OR LegalWorkspace exposes a discrete "AI Briefing" registration that SpaarkeAi opts into.
      Decide; document; implement. If unclear, default to Option L (smaller blast radius for this task; can hoist later).
    </step>
    <step order="6" name="Create shared SECTION_REGISTRY composition">
      Decide the shared lib's exported registry shape:
      - **Sub-step 6a**: Export `PORTABLE_SECTION_REGISTRY: SectionRegistration[]` from `@spaarke/ui-components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/sectionRegistry.ts`. This is the canonical list of portable sections.
      - **Sub-step 6b**: LegalWorkspace's `sectionRegistry.ts` becomes a composition: `[...PORTABLE_SECTION_REGISTRY, dailyBriefingRegistration]` (or whichever local factories it adds).
      - **Sub-step 6c**: SpaarkeAi's WorkspaceHomeTab.tsx imports `PORTABLE_SECTION_REGISTRY` + `buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig` from `@spaarke/ui-components`.
    </step>
    <step order="7" name="Wire WorkspaceHomeTab to use shared infrastructure">
      Rewrite `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceHomeTab.tsx`:
      - Import `buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig` + `PORTABLE_SECTION_REGISTRY` from `@spaarke/ui-components`.
      - Build a `SectionFactoryContext` from SpaarkeAi's environment (webApi via Xrm bootstrap, userId from authenticated session, callbacks for `onOpenWizard`/`onNavigate` using `Xrm.Navigation.navigateTo`).
      - Remove the placeholder `buildFoundationalConfig` and `renderContent: <Text>placeholder</Text>` pattern.
      - Pass the fully-built config to `<WorkspaceShell config={config} />`.
    </step>
    <step order="8" name="Verify standalone LegalWorkspace identical">
      Run `cd src/solutions/LegalWorkspace && npm run build`. Verify build succeeds.
      Manually compare bundle size + section count vs pre-task baseline. Document any drift.
      The standalone LegalWorkspace Code Page MUST be visually identical after this task.
    </step>
    <step order="9" name="Verify SpaarkeAi renders section content">
      Run `cd src/solutions/SpaarkeAi && npm run build`. Verify build succeeds.
      Document the bundle-size delta vs Phase F task 061 baseline (777.6 KB gzip post-deploy).
      Hoisting portable factories may INCREASE SpaarkeAi bundle (now pulls in section component bodies it didn't before). Acknowledge if NFR-12 deviation grows; reference bundle-size assessment.
    </step>
    <step order="10" name="Tests + quality gates">
      - Update or add tests for the hoisted infrastructure if existing patterns exist in shared-lib tests.
      - Run `code-review` skill on modified files.
      - Run `adr-check` skill (ADR-012, ADR-021, ADR-028 compliance).
      - Run dark-mode token grep on any new/modified component files.
    </step>
    <step order="11" name="Redeploy both web resources">
      After build verification:
      - Run `scripts/Deploy-SpaarkeAi.ps1` (redeploys sprk_spaarkeai with the new WorkspaceHomeTab content).
      - Run `scripts/Deploy-LegalWorkspaceCustomPage.ps1` (or equivalent) to redeploy standalone LegalWorkspace.
      - Update deploy memo at `notes/deploys/2026-05-20-deploy.md` with supplemental deploy section.
    </step>
    <step order="12" name="Update task status + TASK-INDEX + project docs">
      - Task 067 POML → completed.
      - TASK-INDEX row 067 → ✅.
      - Update plan.md Risk Register: mark "Bug 2 / ADR-012 cross-cutting limitation" as RESOLVED.
      - Add a `notes/067-shared-lib-hoist-summary.md` documenting the architectural change for the wrap-up lessons-learned.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Source files across 3 solutions</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Modify shared lib + LegalWorkspace + SpaarkeAi files</tool>
    <tool name="Write">New shared lib files; inventory memo; deploy memo append</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">npm install/build commands; deploy script invocations</tool>
    <tool name="Grep">Find import sites, dependency tracing</tool>
    <tool name="Glob">Locate section factory files</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig.ts (NEW — hoisted)</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/sectionRegistry.ts (NEW — PORTABLE_SECTION_REGISTRY export)</output>
    <output type="code">src/client/shared/Spaarke.UI.Components/src/components/WorkspaceShell/sections/*.registration.ts (NEW — hoisted factories)</output>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/sectionRegistry.ts (MODIFIED — composes shared + local)</output>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/LegalWorkspace/src/workspace/buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig.ts (REPLACED with re-export OR deleted if no remaining imports)</output>
    <output type="code">src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceHomeTab.tsx (MODIFIED — uses shared infrastructure)</output>
    <output type="notes">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/drafts/067-factory-inventory.md (NEW — per-factory portability classification)</output>
    <output type="notes">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/notes/067-shared-lib-hoist-summary.md (NEW — architectural change summary)</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">@spaarke/ui-components public barrel exports `buildDynamicWorkspaceConfig` and `PORTABLE_SECTION_REGISTRY`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">@spaarke/ui-components builds clean (tsc) with no new errors.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">LegalWorkspace builds clean (vite) with no new errors; bundle size delta within reasonable bounds.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">LegalWorkspace's sectionRegistry.ts composes [...PORTABLE_SECTION_REGISTRY, ...local].</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Standalone LegalWorkspace, opened in a separate browser tab, renders existing user layouts with the SAME section content as before this task.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Standalone LegalWorkspace shows all 9 layout templates in the wizard (FR-25 backwards compat).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SpaarkeAi WorkspaceHomeTab.tsx no longer uses placeholder renderContent; renders actual section components from the shared registry.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">SpaarkeAi builds clean (vite); bundle size delta documented vs Phase F task 061 baseline (NFR-12 deviation context preserved).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Both web resources redeployed; deploy memo appended.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new accessToken props or state introduced (ADR-028).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No new hex/rgba literals in modified code (ADR-021).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Architectural summary memo at notes/067-shared-lib-hoist-summary.md documents the cross-cutting refactor for project wrap-up.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    This task is the structural response to the operator's "ADR limitation of cross cutting
    components — that needs to be addressed" feedback. After this task, the workspace
    section infrastructure is properly shared per ADR-012; future Code Pages that need to
    embed workspace surfaces can do so via the same shared barrel.

    The dailyBriefing factory decision (Option H vs L in step 5) is documented in the
    factory-inventory memo. If staying solution-local, SpaarkeAi loses Daily Briefing
    until a future task hoists it. If hoisting, SpaarkeAi gets it for free now but the
    shared lib gains a feature dependency.

    Risk highest in steps 4 (hoist factories) and 8 (verify LegalWorkspace identical).
    Any visual regression in standalone LegalWorkspace is a FR-25 violation and must be
    fixed before this task is considered complete.

    Architectural follow-on (NOT in this task, captured for next review):
    The operator also flagged a pane-coordination requirement — "we need to have some
    rule or logic in the code that matches what is in the Workspace pane with what is
    in the Context pane because these work in conjunction (and likewise of course the
    Assistant needs to be aware of what is in the Workspace pane and the Context pane
    b/c the Assistant is directly interacting)". This is a separate architectural
    concern (Assistant ↔ Workspace ↔ Context state coordination) — likely a follow-on
    project or new ADR. Out of scope for task 067.
  </notes>

  <execution>
    Execute via `task-execute` skill. Multi-file refactor — Step 8.0 multi-file work decomposition
    applies. Consider splitting into sub-agents: (a) shared-lib agent (hoist builder + factories);
    (b) LegalWorkspace agent (compose + verify identical); (c) SpaarkeAi agent (wire WorkspaceHomeTab).
    These ARE sequential (each depends on the prior landing), so a single coordinated agent may
    be cleaner than parallel.
  </execution>
</task>
